title: TINKERPOP-3009 Removed redundant SubgraphStrategy filters.
body:
https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TINKERPOP-3009

Note that TraverserGenerators changed a bit because of the filter patterns that were added, thus the assertion adjustments. Basically, rather than adding and(inV()..., outV()...) for every single edge step it's done more strategically such that only the direction not already traversed gets filtered. Also avoids some retesting of vertices if they were already handled.

Before:

```
gremlin> g.withStrategies(SubgraphStrategy.build().
......1>            vertices(hasLabel('x','y','z')).create()).
......2>   V().out().profile()
==>Traversal Metrics
Step                                                               Count  Traversers       Time (ms)    % Dur
=============================================================================================================
TinkerGraphStep(vertex,[~label.within([x, y, z])])                                             0.160    58.50
VertexStep(OUT,edge)                                                                           0.017     6.53
AndStep([[EdgeVertexStep(IN), HasStep([~label.w...                                             0.017     6.19
  EdgeVertexStep(IN)                                                                           0.000
  HasStep([~label.within([x, y, z])])                                                          0.000
  EdgeVertexStep(OUT)                                                                          0.000
  HasStep([~label.within([x, y, z])])                                                          0.000
EdgeVertexStep(IN)                                                                             0.064    23.59
HasStep([~label.within([x, y, z])]) 
```

and after:

```
gremlin> g.withStrategies(new SubgraphStrategy(vertices: __.has("name", P.within("josh", "lop", "ripple")))).V().out().profile()
==>Traversal Metrics
Step                                                               Count  Traversers       Time (ms)    % Dur
=============================================================================================================
TinkerGraphStep(vertex,[name.within([josh, lop,...                     3           3           8.231    95.09
VertexStep(OUT,vertex)                                                 2           2           0.337     3.90
HasStep([name.within([josh, lop, ripple])])                            2           2           0.087     1.01
                                            >TOTAL                     -           -           8.656        -
```

VOTE +1

title: Added Scope to String Functions
body:
Added `Scope` to asString(), length(), toLower(), toUpper(), trim(), lTrim() rTrim(),replace(),split() and substring() to allow String manipulation inside incoming lists.

Added a `StringLocalStep` abstract class for all local scoped functions, except asString() because it's structured slightly differently (doesn't throw type exceptions). 

Some notes on implementation:
- `Scope.local` will accept list traverser and single string value but throw on all other types.
- Non-string lists will also throw.
- Nulls will be passed on as usual

Scope is not added to reverse() step because it overloads as a list function, and local doesn't make sense for lists.

title: Option to force the message to be sent as string instead of bytecode
body:
Hi, here is a small PR that would allow to use the string version instead of the bytecode one.
May reason for that is that some databases, like CosmosDB, doesn't support the bytecode format for now (it was supposed to be ready in 2018...).

This simple option makes most of the job to allow the use of the fluent API with these databases.
I would like to know if there is a place to discuss a change proposal prior to the implementation ? The issues are not open on github.
There are other changes that I would like to propose:
- Allow variant translation (e.g. CosmosDB uses `incr` and `decr` instead of `Order.asc/desc`
- In the __next__ function, add the following code:
  ```python
   if not hasattr(self.last_traverser, "object"):
      object = self.last_traverser
      self.last_traverser = None
      return object
  ```
  The reason is that is it is possible that at this point, the `self.last_traverser` is already the object itself and it would crash to try accessing `object`
- Add a tiny minimal OGM using pydantic that would allow cleaner code (Goblin-OGM exists but it is not maintained, badly documented, ...)
  ```python
  from pydantic import BaseModel

  class Person(BaseModel)
        __label__ = "person"
        name: str
        age: int

  person1 = Person("john", "42")
  person2 = Person("James", "24")
  client.save(person1).save(person2).next()
  # or simply
  # client.save([person1, person2]).next()
  ```
  Nb: We can also image the retrieval to automaticly wrap the result based on the label
- (Improve the general quality of the module)

Most of these changes are already made on my side through a custom library that inject itself into gremlin_python, but it would be better to have it the base module.

title: [TINKERPOP-3008] Update concat() to accept traversal varargs
body:
https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TINKERPOP-3008

This updates `concat(Traversal)` to accept traversal varags and also corrected how it handles inject() child traversals. 

The updated signature is `concat(Traversal, Traversal...)` to disambiguate from `concat(String...)` method call.

Also a small breaking change on how inject child traversals are handled. We mistakenly added special handling, but it is the default behaviour of `inject()` to return the incoming traverser, so we've corrected that:
```
// behavior of child traversal inject as aligned with its current definition & implementation
gremlin> g.inject("a").concat(inject("b"))
==>aa
// wrongly special cased in 3.7.0
gremlin> g.inject("a").concat(inject("b"))
==>ab
// proper way to add a string in concat
gremlin> g.inject("a").concat(constant("b"))
==>ab
```

VOTE +1

title: [TINKERPOP-3004] improve GremlinValueComparator performance
body:
There are 3 reasons for the reduced performance of element comparison compared to 3.5
1. Relatively fast [`BulkSet.Contains`](https://github.com/apache/tinkerpop/blob/ea0bbed85a22ffefc8fa599e9d50ee68d60162fd/gremlin-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tinkerpop/gremlin/process/traversal/Contains.java#L57) replaced with slow iteration and comparison one by one object. Most expensive operation here is building and using of Iterator over incoming `BulkSet`
2. Equality comparison uses [lots of type checking](https://github.com/apache/tinkerpop/blob/32ec7f97c0464cb015bdc7cf766a94e6fbb71210/gremlin-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tinkerpop/gremlin/util/GremlinValueComparator.java#L127). 
3. Equality comparison uses [reflection](https://github.com/apache/tinkerpop/blob/32ec7f97c0464cb015bdc7cf766a94e6fbb71210/gremlin-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tinkerpop/gremlin/util/GremlinValueComparator.java#L142). 

I used test query included in this PR.
Total test execution time for
vanilla 3.7 is 2700ms
with my change is 1000ms
vanilla 3.5 is 200ms

Main impact on execution time is 
Iterator adds ~200 ms
`Compare.eq.test(first, o)` is ~ 2000 ms

I also tried to verify all objects types and than reuse `BulkSet.contains`, execution time was ~550ms, but this doesn't work for all types

title: [TINKERPOP-2423] Do not use XOR in hashCode computation when redundant key is possible
body:
We may want to do away with XOR for hashCode computation for everything, but for now I only limit those whose keys for XOR are very simple and can be duplicate.
Duplicate keys are canceled with each other when XOR is applied, that is the problem and a different Step can be considered as "equal" as consequence.

This CR fixes the issue.

Scala 2.13.11

The Scala team at Lightbend is pleased to announce Scala 2.13.11.

The following changes are highlights of this release:

Collections

  • Faster Vector concatenation (#10159 by @​ansvonwa)
  • New LinkedHashMap/LinkedHashSet implementation (#10221 by @​liang3zy22)

Compatibility

  • Support JDK 20 and 21 by upgrading to ASM 9.5 (#10363, #10184 by @​Philippus)
  • Fix crash reading JDK 21 classfiles (#10397)
  • Support Java 17 sealed in Java sources and classfiles (#10348, #10105 by @​som-snytt)
  • Support Scala 3.3 in TASTy reader (#10299 by @​bishabosha)

Align with Scala 3

  • Accept implicit _, implicit (x: Int) in lambdas, like Scala 3 does (#10327 by @​som-snytt)
  • Deprecate infix type args, as they are dropped in Scala 3 (#10255 by @​som-snytt)
  • Allow eta-expansion of methods with dependent types (#10166)
  • Abstract parent copy does not suspend case copy (#10085 by @​som-snytt)
  • Don't GLB binders of type patterns, use the type directly (#10247)
  • Under -Xsource:3, warn that inherited members no longer take precedence over outer definitions in Scala 3 (#10220, #10339)
  • Under -Xsource:3, adjust 2.13.9 change to ignore override type for whitebox macro expansion (#10188 by @​som-snytt)
  • Under -Xsource:3, use narrowest type for pt of override (#10198 by @​som-snytt)
  • Under -Xsource:3, warn about change to parenless lambda parens (#10320 by @​som-snytt)

Lints and warnings

  • Lint select from Unit, or Int that incurs widening (#10372 by @​som-snytt)
  • Lint for integral divisions that are widened to a float (#10369 by @​som-snytt)
  • Lint if args adapted to Unit and discarded (#10150 by @​som-snytt)
  • Warn that implicit should have explicit type (#10083 by @​som-snytt)

Other notable changes

  • Disallow mixins where super calls bind to vals (#10268)
  • Make scalac's argument-file processing more like javac's in handling spaces and line breaks (#10319 by @​som-snytt)
  • Bump JLine and JNA versions (#10318)
  • javabootclasspath supersedes jrt (#10336 by @​som-snytt)
  • Report total errors on stderr (#10272 by @​som-snytt)
  • Fix pathologically slow compilation of some pattern matches since 2.13.7 (#10258 by @​KisaragiEffective)
  • Provide equals and hashCode on IterableWrapper again (fixing 2.13.9 regression) (#10205 by @​som-snytt)
  • Improvements to -Vimplicits; errors now show complete implicit search tree (#9944 by @​tribbloid)
  • -Vprint defaults to -Vprint:typer; phases may be prefixed with ~ to mean "before and after" (#10173 by @​som-snytt)
